  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, combine the sliced ham, crushed garlic, shredded mozzarella cheese, chopped fresh parsley, salt, pepper, paprika, and dried oregano.",
    "Mix well to combine.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together the chopped onion, chopped fresh dill, and breadcrumbs.",
    "Sprinkle the onion mixture evenly over the top of the ham mixture.",
    "Drizzle the olive oil over the top.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Let the dish rest for 5 minutes before serving."
